Superhero family! #halloween2020

Pumpkin carving night. Jacob snapped the bottom photo of us!! Had NO idea until I looked at my phone later 🤣

These 2!!! 🧡 🎃 
#halloween2020
Our fridge. It’s messy, chaotic, and absolutely PERFECT ❤️ #jacobsworksofart #dayhomecreations
She’s always pulling Dido’s glasses off his face, so he put them on her! 🤣 #disneyUP
“Mama” “Mama’s mini” 💕

October 16th with a forecast of heavy snow and my marigold garden for mom still looks beautiful! 🧡 This year I planted a bunch of my garden from seeds that I could order online, including these! And they’ve never looked more full and beautiful! #momwouldlovethem #herfavouriteflower
💗Month 8💗

8 months old!!! She hasn’t started crawling (mainly because I never want her to stop being my potatoe baby 😭) But this month she started saying “Mom” and my heart explodes each and every time!!! Gah! I love you Julianna ❤️

I’ve had this 11 year old bottle of wine in our wine fridge for years. I was always waiting for an important occasion to open it. Dad stopped by this evening on what would have been his and mom’s 50th wedding anniversary. So we enjoyed a glass (or two..) in honour of them and this special day 💕
The crunchy leaves were mind blowing...and of course, tasty 🤦🏻‍♀️
Took the kids to @myprairiegardens today 🧡 Trying to make the most of this weather before it’s gone!
First sibling bath 😍 They both got upset when it was was time to get out! Seeing how much they love each other warms my heart!
😍 So happy that perma-frown baby is gone (most of the time...😂)
Perfect fall family day at the @yegcornmaze 🧡

This first day of fall yesterday had me doing some serious reminiscing. A few months ago I was so upset over what this summer would be with everything shut down or cancelled. Now it’s crazy to say...that may have been the best summer of my life. Normally this type A planner is stressed about planning each festival and event into our schedule. It was so REFRESHING to have no plans!!! We found so much joy in simpler things. Exploring outside, water fights, walks, parks, family dinner every single night and those sanity saving distanced bonfires! I hope when the world starts going back to how it used to be, I can remember how wonderful it was to just slow down and enjoy the little moments 💕#pleaseremindmethough #weknowplannerstephwillreturn
Just a few favourites from Julianna’s 6 month photos (so hard to pick 10!) Thanks @roughley_originals for capturing this amazingly fun age ❤️
My incredible mother in law and I started a new tradition today. No more birthday gifts and instead we will go for a nice dinner together to celebrate both of us each September 💕

First day of outdoor “Forest School”. It may have started a little rough with some tears from our nervous boy. But the teachers at @wildchildedmonton were SO great and he’s already asking if he can go back tomorrow! 🌳 🍃 💚
💗Month 7💗
Jules is 7 months! Our little chunk is getting more of her silly, loving, sweet personality each and everyday. Man I love her! 😍
Loooong overdue date night with my love! ❤️
Happy early birthday to me!!! Meet Hanna the Hybrid Highlander 😍 #toyotahighlander2020
Loving life ❤️

Preparing for Julianna’s baptism tomorrow and we’re trying on some pretty special pieces she’s going to wear to church. The left is my baptism outfit, the right is MY DAD’S 73 YEAR OLD baptismal gown!!! #fromgenerationtogeneration #specialkeepsakes

I always thought these things looked insane, but why not give it a shot? SO glad we did! Julianna had the best day with her buddy Nori kicking and splashing with non stop smiles and laughs. Thanks @thebabyspa.sherwoodpark for giving us a fun and safe activity to do with our babies 💕#spaday

node.text: Hot tip: Schedule your time slot for the @edmontonvalleyzoo when it’s raining! Way less busy and way more animals come out! #familytime #maskscanthidesmiles #juliannawastheretoo
Today we dressed up Julianna in a dress that grandma’s mom knit for auntie Angie 49 years ago and it was so special 💕
💗Month 6💗

6 MONTHS!!! 😭 It hit me pretty hard that my baby is 1/2 a year old already. But what a month it’s been!! First solids, ears pierced, sitting independently, finally rolling both ways (without getting her arm stuck) and most exciting, sleep training which means I feel human again!! 💕
Life is good 💗💙

HAPPY BIRTHDAY to my stud of a husband! 😘❤️ Will is impossible to shop for, so this year I did something a little different. I got him a cameo from some of our favourite reality TV shows! @sierra_dawn_ from Survivor, @zachnichols15 from The Challenge and @adampike444 from Big Brother Canada. The surprise appearances from @janglim21 and @jennacompono were an exciting bonus!!!

Finally got Julianna into a pool and I think we have a second water baby! Super impressed with the measures Clareview Rec Center is taking to keep everyone distanced and safe ❤️ It was also pretty awesome having the kid pool all to ourselves!

I’ve been going to weekly @mommyconnectionsyeg_w outdoor distanced sessions with an absolutely wonderful group of ladies ❤️ A few weeks ago was a mommy and me photo session with the incredible @roughley_originals

Every year I try to add 1 or 2 perennials in my yard to make my gardening easier. This year I decided to add this beauty to my front yard. I have a couple of these hydrangeas already and they’re my absolute favourite type of flower: easy maintenance and they look beautiful with blooms all summer long (and they look pretty awesome in the fall too when the flowers dry up) 🌸❤️
Ok. I realize my newsfeed is all Jules all the time. But seriously!! Look at this beautiful homemade romper my wonderful friend Kim made 😍
She’s as excited about this sun as mama is!! ☀️ #allthegums
Big day for Jules! #firstsolids
One week ago this kid absolutely refused to sit on a bike! Now he’s asking to bike to Dido’s house and the park! Thanks @pedalheads
💗Month 5💗

It’s insane to me that Julianna is already 5 months old! The best part of this month was the affection and love she’s starting to show us. She lights us when Jacob walks into a room, she gets sad when mommy or daddy walk away, and she’s always giving the BEST sloppy kisses 😘
The best Saturdays are spent at the beach ☀️ #cherishedfamilymoments #makingmemories #thattanlinethough

One of my favourite things to do, while on mat leave with Jacob, were the @xtendbarreedmonton baby barre classes. I was SO looking forward to doing these with Jules too. Unfortunately, Xtend is closing their doors 😭 I was so happy we got to do one final class tonight together 💕 We’ll miss you guys!!
Loving this piece in Julianna’s nursery as much as I did the day it was delivered (on the day she was born!) @wildcombdesigns

Happy Father’s Day babe! Thank you for being the most hands on, goofy, supportive and loving daddy! You are an absolute light in all of our lives! Whether it’s dance parties in the living room, or doing anything to get those belly giggles, we’re all so lucky to have you in our lives! 💕
Just a few recent favorites 💕#camerahappy #mylittledoll #finallysmiling
💗Month 4💗

4 months!!! And it’s been the best month by far! Jules is becoming a little chunk like her brother 😍, her personality is starting to shine through and her giggles are absolutely the greatest sound on earth!

We had so many troubles trying to buy a new or used play set, so Will decided to build his own!!! He put SO MANY hours into this thing with so much passion towards detail and making it “high quality”. There’s even a rock climbing wall on the back and he’s waiting on some fun accessories to add for the kids! I’ve never been more impressed! We’re so lucky 😍
#blackouttuesday #listening #learning
My whole world! 💕

It’s so hard to believe it’s been 5 years since we said I do! It’s not easy to find the words to express how grateful I am to have you as my husband. William, thank you for always being my rock and truly being my other half 💕 “Everything’s better when we’re together”
Our handsome and wild little dude 😎
I mean come on!!! 😍
💗Month 3💗

3 months! People have said this isolation makes you more grateful for the little things and wow, was that ever true this month! Our perma-frown baby started smiling!!!! It’s incredible how the shittiest day can immediately turn around when Jules gives me her big gummy smile 😭 I’m so grateful for the light she brings to us each and every day. 💕

Thank you @allenavw (and @themaybejamie) for spending your Mother’s Day delivering these amazing @fabloomosity arrangements to our main mommas. I’m so grateful for your friendship, generosity and constant support as we do this mom thing together 💕 #momtribe #icriedsohard
I have too much time on my hands right now...
Today’s dress brought to you by Eatons, circa 1987 #minime #mamasdress
Covid hair, don’t care

Maybe it was COVID who broke up this band, maybe it was drama over the lead singer spot! 😂 I’m reminiscing over old videos and realizing how much more I’ll cherish these play dates when this is all over #TBT #wemissyou #fucovid19
We have the best/most talented neighbour! Thank you heather for the home made dragon for Jacob! ❤️

When my cousin Christina @happyorchidphotography came to meet Julianna from a distance, she also took some front porch photos of our family ❤️ She took these from our sidewalk at least 20 feet away! It’s a great way to capture this strange time we’re in and definitely something surreal to show/talk about with Julianna when she grows up!
💗Month 2💗

2 months old!! This entire month was spent physically distancing at home. The isolation really sucks and there have been many tears shed. BUT we’re blessed to be healthy, safe and we get so much extra special bonding time! Plus, the beginning of her life will be a crazy story to talk to her about one day!

HAPPY EASTER EVERYONE!! This year was definitely different to keep everyone safe and healthy. But we still had a wonderful weekend with zoom dinners, an egg hunt in the snow, a super excited toddler after finding his basket, distanced visits with loved ones and so many delicious treats dropped off on our porch! We may be physically isolated right now, but I found that the love and appreciation for family was stronger this year than ever before 💕 
#icantwaittohugyouall #easter2020
Did a bunch of front porch drop offs for some friends and family the last couple days. But the same sentiment goes out to all of you 💕 #screwyoucovid19 #stayhome
These sibling moments 😭❤️ #mywholeheart

I thought it was safer for Dido if I dropped off his care package instead of Will yesterday. So I took the 1 minute drive to his house (for the first time “out” without the kids since Jules was born) and I got to say hello...from a safe distance. We’re both feeling pretty lonely and isolated, so it filled my heart to see my daddy! 💕 #newnormal #physicaldistancingsocialconnecting

I don’t really know how to express all the feelings I’m having...but here goes! I’m of course grateful to be on maternity leave right now, but I also feel guilty that I’m not there with my work family. Everyday I am worried about my RAH and NE coworkers who put themselves at risk for the safety of others. It breaks my heart that the public is told to quarantine for 14 days after coming into contact with COVID-19, and my coworkers have to make the choice of returning home to their loved ones knowing they came in contact. I’ve had some friends who have decided to isolate themselves from their own children so that they can continue helping the public. So, THANK YOU! Thank you to the Nurses, Doctors, EMS, RTs, Social workers, Unit clerks, Service workers, Environmental services, DI techs, Registration, Educators and Management. Thank you for your bravery, your commitment, your skills, and your strength during this time. Thank you for putting the needs of the public above your own. Thank you for truly being heroes! #covid_19 #therealheroes
💗Month 1💗

And somehow Julianna is 1 month old already!!! She may have had a perma-frown the first few days of her life 😂 but she quickly turned into the most beautiful thing I have ever laid my eyes on. This month has been a whirlwind getting used to our new normal. But we are so blessed to have a dream newborn this time around with Jacob as an amazingly helpful and loving big brother. It’s true what they say, your heart really does grow when you have a second child 💕

🙌🏻 International women’s day 🙌🏻 I’m blessed to be surrounded by so many incredible women in my family and friends who inspire me daily 💕 But now I am so grateful that I have this little woman in my life who I get the honour of raising into a strong, confident woman herself! #iwd2020 #tinybutmighty
🎵 Do you want to build a snowman? ❤️
On February 13 at 5:48AM, our family became complete as we welcomed Julianna Gloria Stephanie Rivera into our lives. She was 7lbs 1oz of perfection and she is so deeply loved already.
Very well may be the last bump photo we ever take, so might as well have fun 🤣 #39weeks

The woman’s body is amazing and pregnancy is so incredible. I never feel more beautiful than I do when I am pregnant. I am trying my best to ignore those aches and pains at the end, and instead I am soaking in these last few days of those beautiful moments. The kicks, the flutters, the hiccups, the connection 💕 #37weeks #goingtomissthis #bumppic #pregnancyisbeautiful

36 weeks today! And last day of work today 😭 Lots of people told me I was crazy to go back to work super pregnant with a broken foot, but I’m so happy I did! Grateful for management who let me hobble around the department, and grateful for my RAH ER family that keeps me LOVING my job despite any struggles we face 💕I’m definitely going to miss work, but I’m also so excited for what’s next 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦

Big day in the Rivera household! Jacob had his first day of Sadochok (Ukrainian Playschool) 😭 He ran right into class and started playing with the kids without looking back. My mama heart was so very proud 💕
BYEEEEEEEE ✌🏻 I won’t miss you! #justintime #1monthtobaby #stillhealing #physiolife
What a day! Thank you to everyone who came to celebrate Jacob’s 3rd birthday @blippi style! 💙 🧡
